    <div id="School-Day" class="content-section">
      <h1>School Day</h1>
      <p>Learn about our daily schedule and activities for nursery students.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Arrival & Welcome:</strong> 7:30am – 8:00am. Children are greeted and settle in with morning routines.</li>
        <li><strong>Circle Time:</strong> 8:00am – 8:30am. Songs, stories, and sharing to start the day together.</li>
        <li><strong>Learning Centers:</strong> 8:30am – 10:00am. Hands-on activities in art, science, literacy, and numeracy.</li>
        <li><strong>Snack & Outdoor Play:</strong> 10:00am – 10:45am. Healthy snacks and supervised play in our safe playground.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Activities:</strong> 10:45am – 12:00pm. Music, dance, and crafts to encourage self-expression.</li>
        <li><strong>Lunch & Rest:</strong> 12:00pm – 1:30pm. Nutritious meals followed by quiet time or napping.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon Exploration:</strong> 1:30pm – 2:30pm. Group games, story time, and review of the day.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick-Up:</strong> 2:30pm – 3:00pm. Children prepare to go home, with feedback for parents.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/successful-schoolgirl_1098-13593.avif" alt="Nursery Activities" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
    </div>

    <div id="Curriculum" class="content-section">
      <h1>Curriculum</h1>
      <p>Explore our comprehensive curriculum designed for young learners.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language & Literacy:</strong> Early reading, storytelling, and communication skills.</li>
        <li><strong>Numeracy:</strong> Introduction to numbers, shapes, and patterns through fun activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Science & Discovery:</strong> Exploring the world with simple experiments and nature walks.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Arts:</strong> Drawing, painting, music, and movement to inspire imagination.</li>
        <li><strong>Social & Emotional Learning:</strong> Building friendships, empathy, and confidence.</li>
        <li><strong>Faith & Values:</strong> Instilling Christian values and character development.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/other-uniform.webp" alt="Nursery Curriculum" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
